          <p class="apn-hydr-product-price">$44.99</p>
          <p class="apn-hydr-product-desc">Creatine plus complete electrolytes combined. For athletes with high training volumes who need intracellular and extracellular hydration addressed simultaneously.</p>

          <div style="display:grid;gap:12px;margin-top:16px;">
            <div style="background:#F8F8F8;padding:14px 16px;border-radius:3px;">
              <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">The Mechanism</p>
              <p class="apn-hydr-product-meta">Creatine monohydrate increases intramuscular water content by pulling water into muscle cells via osmotic pressure. This increases cell volume by approximately 1 to 2%, which directly improves intracellular hydration status and anabolic signaling. Combined with the extracellular electrolyte panel, Replenish Plus addresses hydration at both the plasma level (electrolytes) and the muscle cell level (creatine). At high training volumes, both compartments need to be optimized.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#F8F8F8;padding:14px 16px;border-radius:3px;">
              <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">Dose and Timing</p>
              <p class="apn-hydr-product-meta"><strong>1 serving in 20 oz of water, 60 to 90 minutes pre-training.</strong> Replaces Replenish (standard) for athletes taking daily creatine, consolidating both supplements into one pre-training drink.</p>
