      <div class="apn-tier-block-h" data-tier="champion" style="display:block;">
        <div class="apn-hydr-product-card">
          <p class="apn-hydr-product-label">Advanced Product (Champion Tier)</p>
          <h3 class="apn-hydr-product-name">Replenish Plus</h3>
          <p class="apn-hydr-product-price">$44.99</p>
          <p class="apn-hydr-product-desc">Champion-level hydration architecture uses Replenish Plus pre-training and standard Replenish post-training to separate the creatine loading from the recovery window. Full protocol.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SUPPORTING PRODUCT -->
      <div class="apn-hydr-product-card">
        <p class="apn-hydr-product-label">Supporting Product</p>
        <h3 class="apn-hydr-product-name">Recharge — Creatine Monohydrate</h3>
        <p class="apn-hydr-product-price">$39.99</p>
        <p class="apn-hydr-product-desc">5g daily creatine monohydrate. Increases intramuscular water retention by 1 to 2%, directly improving cellular hydration as a complementary mechanism to electrolyte-based plasma volume management.</p>

        <div style="display:grid;gap:12px;margin-top:16px;">
          <div style="background:#F8F8F8;padding:14px 16px;border-radius:3px;">
            <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">The Mechanism</p>
            <p class="apn-hydr-product-meta">Creatine is stored in muscle tissue as phosphocreatine, and it is hydrophilic: it draws water into the muscle cell. After 28 days of 5g daily intake (muscle saturation), intramuscular water content increases by 1 to 2%. This is not the same as bloating. It is increased intracellular hydration in the muscle compartment where protein synthesis and energy production occur. For athletes whose hydration gap includes cellular dehydration (not just plasma dehydration), creatine addresses the compartment that electrolytes alone cannot reach.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background:#F8F8F8;padding:14px 16px;border-radius:3px;">
            <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">Dose and Timing</p>
            <p class="apn-hydr-product-meta"><strong>5g daily.</strong> Timing is not critical for creatine. Consistency is. Take it with your post-training meal on training days or with any meal on rest days. Full muscle saturation is achieved after 28 days of consistent daily use without a loading phase.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
