  <!-- MODULE 6: YOUR 30-DAY CHALLENGE -->
  <div id="apn-hydr-m6" style="background:#0D0D0D;padding:80px 24px;">
    <div style="max-width:680px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:4px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:16px;display:block;">The Commitment</span>
      <h2 style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:40px;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:-0.02em;color:#F8FAFB;margin-bottom:24px;line-height:1.2;">The Gap Closes When You Decide It Does</h2>
      <div style="width:64px;height:3px;background:#06A5C5;margin:0 0 40px;"></div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:48px;">
        <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:24px;">4 Measurable Habit Targets</p>

        <div class="apn-hydr-habit">
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-num">01</div>
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-text">
            <h4>Hit Your Daily Water Target Every Day</h4>
            <p>Bodyweight in pounds divided by 2 equals your minimum daily ounces. Plus 16 to 24 oz per hour of training. This is not a suggestion. It is the minimum your body requires to perform the physiological work you are asking of it. Measure it daily for 30 days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="apn-hydr-habit">
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-num">02</div>
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-text">
            <h4>Electrolytes 90 Minutes Before Every Training Session</h4>
            <p>20 oz with electrolytes, 90 minutes before every session. Not most sessions. Every session. This is where the early-session fog is fixed and the cardiovascular handicap is removed. Miss this window and you train dehydrated regardless of everything else you do.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="apn-hydr-habit">
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-num">03</div>
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-text">
            <h4>Sip 6 to 8 oz Every 20 Minutes During Training</h4>
            <p>Small sips throughout. Not gulps at the end. The protocol replaces fluid continuously to prevent the plasma volume drop that causes second-half performance decline. Set a timer if you need to until it is automatic. Most athletes build this habit within 2 to 3 weeks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="apn-hydr-habit">
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-num">04</div>
          <div class="apn-hydr-habit-text">
            <h4>16 to 24 oz With Electrolytes Within 30 Minutes Post-Training</h4>
            <p>The post-training replenishment window closes within 30 minutes. After that, recovery begins to proceed in a cellular environment that is still fluid-depleted. This habit ensures that protein synthesis, glycogen resynthesis, and tissue repair all operate with full hydration support from the moment they begin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
